Italy is set to become the (first country in Europe) to offer female workers paid menstrual leave! Women who suffer from dysmenorrhea, a condition that makes periods extremely painful will have three days of paid leave every month! I wish they allowed this in America!😕🇺🇸
————————————————————
As well as period pain in the pelvis or abdomen, other symptoms of dysmenorrhea include back pain, diarrhea, and nausea. It is more common in people with heavy or irregular periods, those who have a low body weight and for period-havers with a low body weight.

Paid period pain leave is already in action in Japan, Taiwan, South Korea and Indonesia. 
Via @konbini 
#GirlProblems #GirlPower #PeriodProblems #Women #Cramps #GirlsBeLike #WorldNews #Employment #Work #Rest #Italy #InstaglamNews
